                                <h2 class="text-center mt-0">Leggo Manzoni in <i>Resto del Carlino</i></h2>
                                <p>
                                    <strong>March 11, 2025</strong>. Today, the newspaper <i>Il Resto del Carlino</i> has
                                    published an in-depth article on the project "Leggo Manzoni/Wo-Dú Manzoni. Reading
                                    <i>The Betrothed</i> in Beijing". In the article, journalist Martina Spaggiari
                                    describes the Alma Mater initiative that will lead to the creation of a digital
                                    edition of Alessandro Manzoni's novel with a parallel Chinese text.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    The article highlights the cultural and innovative value of the project, with Prof.
                                    Paola Italia explaining: "<i>The Betrothed</i> is the only required novel in our
                                    schools, and certainly the least loved." She also points out how the project is part
                                    of a path started years ago: "Manzoni became a digital humanities case study and in
                                    2014 the website <i><a href="https://alessandromanzoni.org">alessandromanzoni.org</a></i> was born, a pioneering operation which later
                                    inspired all other monographic sites."
                                </p>
