                                <h2 class="text-center mt-0">Alma Leopardi 2024 – 2nd Edition: Il libro delle Canzoni</h2>
                                <p>
                                    <strong>November 28, 2024</strong>. At the Academy of Sciences of Bologna (sala Manfredi, via Zamboni 31, Bologna) the second edition of Alma Leopardi
                                    took place, dedicated to the "<i>libro delle Canzoni</i>". The event was divided into two main
                                    sessions:
                                </p>

                                <p>The <strong>First Session</strong> (10:00–13:00), coordinated by Gisele Marozzi and
                                    Roberta Priore, featured talks by Christian Genetelli on "<i>Un libro non come gli
                                        altri?</i>" and Maria Maddalena Lombardi on "<i>Alle Canzoni sono da fare
                                        alcune prose: i 'paratesti' del 1824</i>". Emilio Russo presented "<i>Sugli
                                        autografi delle canzoni. Descrizioni e note critiche</i>".</p>

                                <p>The <strong>Second Session</strong> (14:30–18:30), coordinated by Ilaria Burattini
                                    and Marcello Dani, included a talk by Giorgio Panizza on "<i>Immaginazione:
                                        morte e impeto</i>" and the presentation of "<i>Canzoni di Giacomo Leopardi. Tomo
                                    I: testi editi e documenti dell'officina del 1824</i>", edited by Ilaria Burattini and Roberta Priore,
                                    with an introduction by Christian Genetelli (Bites, 2024). The day ended with the
                                    presentation of the volume "<i>E roverar le stelle ad una ad una. Conti</i>" (Milan,
                                    BUR, 2024) and "<i>Manzoni and Leopardi in Digital. Ideas and Projects for
                                        Schools</i>" (Clueb, 2024).
                                </p>
