                                <h2 class="text-center mt-0">Manzoni and Leopardi in Digital: Ideas and Projects for
                                    Schools</h2>
                                <p>
                                    <strong>September 19 & 21, 2023</strong>. At CUBO in Porta Europa (Piazza Vieira de
                                    Mello 5, Bologna) the SOFIA-accredited teacher training course "<i>Manzoni and
                                        Leopardi in Digital: Ideas and Projects for Schools</i>" was held. The event,
                                    organized by the University of Bologna "Alma Mater" in collaboration with CUBO, the
                                    business museum of the Unipol Group, as part of PRIN Manzoni 2020 and PRIN Leopardi
                                    2020, was attended by many experts in the field.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    Among the presentations dedicated to Manzoni: the LECTIO MAGISTRALIS by Salvatore
                                    Silvano Nigro on "Manzoni today", the presentation of the Manzoni Online portal and
                                    its educational applications by Prof. Giulia Raboni, and the talk by Prof. Paola
                                    Italia on "Why still <i>The Betrothed</i> in school?". Special attention was paid to
                                    digital tools for teaching, including Leggo Manzoni, Philoeditor, the "Sposi
                                    promessi" on Spotify, and the use of Voyant Tools for <i>The Betrothed</i>.
                                </p>
